Proximity sensor using HC-SR04 and Arduino Uno R3.
When an object is within 2cm of the sensor, an alarm will sound. 
Lights will progressively turn on the closer the object is to the sensor. 
Volume buttons allow the user to increase and decrease the volume of the alarm.

Connections:
HC-SR04:
Power - 5V
Trig - PORTB0
Echo - PORTB1
Gnd - GND 

Buzzer:
Positive - PORTB2
Negative - GND

Volume Up Button:
In - PORTD2
Out - GND

Volume Down Button:
In - PORTD3
Out - GND

Lights:
From Green to Red - PORTC0 to PORTC5